%N A395019 Decimal expansion of sqrt(105)/5 - 1.
%C A395019 The mode of the distribution of distances between two points in a unit ball. The probability density function is f(x) = 3*x^2 - 9*x^3/4 + 3*x^5/16, its mean is 36/35, and its median is A395020.
%H A395019 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/BallLinePicking.html">Ball Line Picking</a>.		
%H A395019 <a href="/index/Al#algebraic_02">Index entries for algebraic numbers, degree 2</a>.
%F A395019 Minimal polynomial: 5*x^2 + 10*x - 16.
%e A395019 1.049390153191919676644207736104210398147006532690966...
%t A395019 RealDigits[Sqrt[105]/5 - 1, 10, 120][[1]]
%o A395019 (PARI) list(len) = my(c = 2*(quadgen(105)-3)/5); digits(floor(10^len * c));
%Y A395019 Cf. A093530, A093531, A176461, A394605 (disk), A394607 (square), A395018 (cube), A395020 (median).
